Governor Mai Mala Buni of Yobe State has approved for the placement of restriction on the movement of vehicles across the state for a duration of 11 hours. The governor’s Director General on Press affairs, Abdullahi Bego disclosed this in a press statement to newsmen on Saturday. He noted that the restrictions was part of security arrangements for a secure and hitch-free Eid-el-Kabir prayers due to be observed tomorrow, Sunday. The statement explained that restriction on vehicular movement starts from 11.00pm tonight (Saturday August 10th, 2019) to 10.00am on Sunday, August 11th. “His Excellency, Governor Buni wishes all the people of the State an acceptable and blessed Eid,” he added. Sallah: Yobe restricts vehicular movement for 12-hour Yobe restricts movement for peaceful celebration Be your brother’s keepers – Gaidam Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin